G
g \in G
\alpha \in R
g_1,g_2 \in G
(g\alpha)(h)=\alpha(g^{-1}h) \ \ \ \ \ \forall h \in G
(g_1g_2 \alpha)(h)=(g_1 \alpha)(h) . (g_2 \alpha)(h) \ \ \ (*)
(g_1g_2 \alpha)(h)= \alpha(g_2^{-1}g_1^{-1}h) 
(g_1 \alpha)(h) . (g_2 \alpha)(h)=\alpha(g_1^{-1}h)\alpha(g_2^{-1}h)
(g_1 g_2)\alpha = g_1 (g_2 \alpha).
